Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.59,0:00:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long heard of Zǐjìng speak of your talents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.84,0:00:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm honored to meet you today and wanted to ask your advice face to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.10,0:00:48.52,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,500,3300,4000)\pos(1227.121,752.8)}Zhūgě Liàng\NStyled: Kǒngmíng
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.61,0:00:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I am only of modest ability, \Nplease forgive my boorishness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.32,0:00:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Since you, sir, have been assisting \NLiú of Yù-Province, battling Cáo Cāo at Xinye.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.06,0:00:53.52,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1179.36,711.583)}Sūn Quán \NStyled: Zhòngmóu
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.89,0:00:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely you must know of Cáo Cāo's actual strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.03,0:01:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you not know how many troops the Cao army has altogether?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.67,0:01:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With cavalry, infantry, and naval troops combined: more than a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.91,0:01:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it's not a trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.55,0:01:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It is no trick. Cáo Cāo initially had 200,000 Qing-Province troops.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.69,0:01:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He gained 500,000 or 600,000 by defeating Yuan Shao —
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.48,0:01:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,, — 300,000 or 400,000 via recruiting in the Central Plains —
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.19,0:01:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,, — and 200,000 and 300,000 via surrendered soldiers from Jing Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.00,0:01:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Calculating from this, it is no less than a million and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.80,0:01:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I only said a million so as not to scare everyone here at Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.58,0:01:45.80,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(208,752)}Huáng Gài \NStyled: Gōngfù
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.94,0:01:52.94,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(252,714)}Lǔ Sù \NStyled: Zǐjìng
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.56,0:02:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How many generals are under Cáo Cāo?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:08.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Counting crafty, sharp advisors, \Nand capable, veteran officers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.54,0:02:10.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Hardly less than one or two thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.50,0:02:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After taking Jīng Province, does Cáo Cāo have other plans?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.51,0:02:20.26,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why else, other than to take Jiangdong —
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.26,0:02:23.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— is he constructing defenses along the river and preparing warships?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.78,0:02:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Since he indeed wants to conquer us —
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,, — War, or peace? \NWhy not, sir, decide this for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.53,0:02:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Chaos abounds in the world, \Nand lords contest for their place —
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.16,0:02:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And today's Cáo Cāo's reputation is mighty and his strength seems invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.74,0:02:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Although Lord Líu Bèi continues to struggle, he's been defeated repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.64,0:02:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I would suggest the General to measure first  —
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.75,0:03:01.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — If with the peoples of Wú and Yue, you can contend with Cáo Cāo  —
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:03.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — then might as well break off ties now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:07.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If you feel your foundations are weak  —
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.40,0:03:11.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — Why not kneel to his rule and avoid slaughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.66,0:03:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, I said this to the men of Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.70,0:03:21.40,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(248,728)}Zhāng Zhāo\NStyled: Zǐbù
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.03,0:03:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone seems quite willing to surrender to Cáo Cāo,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.94,0:03:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,General, why not follow Heaven's will and the people's wishes, and seek peace and ease?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.13,0:03:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If it is indeed as you say, why does Líu Xuande not surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.98,0:03:55.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,In history, when Qí-State's Tían Hēng  —
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.07,0:04:02.24,Note (Potential style?),NTP,0,0,0,,Note: Tían Hēng was one of many leaders of the rebellions against the late \NQin Dynasty in 209-207 BCE, and was a member of the Qí-State's royal family.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.84,0:03:59.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,  — led five hundred warriors to an island, and swore never to surrender,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.07,0:04:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All five hundred heroically kept their oaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Uncle Líu is of imperial lineage!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,His talent is unparalleled, he is admired by all. If he is defeated, then it is the will of Heaven.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.76,0:04:13.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Rather be as Tían Hēng and break like jade —
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.94,0:04:17.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,, — so how could he kneel and beg, \Nand go to serve the nation's villain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.67,0:04:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, that was far too wanton!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.14,0:04:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I admonished you many times, but you refused to listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.51,0:04:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, if my lord was not magnanimous, he would surely chastise you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.88,0:04:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words, sir, are entirely too contemptuous of my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.49,0:04:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does Sun Zhongmou have such little forbearance?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.63,0:05:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Though I have the plan to defeat Cáo Cāo, \Nhe refused to ask, so why should I tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.40,0:05:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If your plan to defeat Cáo Cāo is so good, then I earnestly ask you to tell me now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.54,0:05:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,In my view, Cáo Cāo's million-man army —
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.61,0:05:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,— is but a horde of ants.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.65,0:05:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I need but wave my hand, and the million Cáo troops are but dust and powder.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.02,0:05:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please wait a moment— let me bring my lord to hear this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.27,0:05:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Libelous, that Kongming!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.20,0:05:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, I too have thus criticized Kǒngmíng—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.82,0:05:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,— yet he laughed sire as shallow-minded in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems that Kǒngmíng already has a plan to defeat Cáo Cāo in his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.99,0:05:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He would not say this lightly, so my lord, why not seek to learn this from him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.90,0:06:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So Kǒngmíng already has a strategy, \Nand purposefully used wordplay to goad me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.67,0:06:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shallow-minded, and nearly put great matters at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.38,0:06:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us go!  My lord, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.62,0:06:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Sleeping Dragon  —
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.85,0:06:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My words were offensive, may the general please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.93,0:06:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Servants!  Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.38,0:06:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare a banquet in the rear hall, to host the Sleeping Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.03,0:06:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes sir!\N-Sir, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.94,0:06:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Please
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.05,0:08:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, does sir also enjoy listening to music?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.79,0:08:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Sleeping Dragon is talented in old musics.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.70,0:08:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When in Longzhong, he was skilled in playing the {\i1}Liángfùyín{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.66,0:08:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah no, I merely enjoy music.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.57,0:08:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, sir, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.08,0:08:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Pity that Gōngjǐng is not with us —
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.85,0:08:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,— else, Sir Sleeping Dragon would have met a kindred spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.56,0:08:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long heard of his charms.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.93,0:08:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the children's songs of Jiangdong say thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.70,0:08:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16.318}{\i1}'If the song has err, Zhōu-láng can take care.'{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.90,0:08:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But, pray tell, where is Gōngjǐng now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.40,0:08:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I ordered him to Lake Fanyang, to conduct naval exercises.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, please —
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.42,0:09:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,At the start of all this, many men rose and each dominated a region.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.33,0:09:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, Yuan Shao, Yuan Shu, Lu Bu, Líu Biao and others, have all perished—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.23,0:09:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Only me, Liu of Yu-Province, and Cáo Cāo remain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot cede all the lands of Wú to another—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,— But since Líu Bèi was just recently defeated, how could he resist Cáo Cāo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.99,0:09:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Though my lord is defeated, Guan Yunchang still leads ten thousand elite troops—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.75,0:09:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,— While Líu Qi also has ten thousand soldiers at Jiangxia.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.17,0:10:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As well , Cáo Cāos's army, having marched south over such long distances, are extremely exhausted—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.74,0:10:07.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Not long before, while pursuing my lord—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.78,0:10:11.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— His light cavalry ran 300{\i1}li {\i0}in a single day and night —
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.22,0:10:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,— As they say, the bolt at the end of a strong crossbow's range cannot pierce even raw silk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.42,0:10:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, northern troops are unskilled at naval combat—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.62,0:10:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,— while the people of Jing-Province are unwilling to serve Cáo Cāo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.00,0:10:24.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If the General and my lord could unite in purpose —
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.86,0:10:26.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— then Cáo Cāo will surely be defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.19,0:10:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If Cáo Cāo is beaten, then he will return north.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.14,0:10:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,With the waxing might of Jing-Province and Eastern Wú —
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.12,0:10:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,— we can stand as the legs of a crucible,\N in a balance of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.11,0:10:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Victory or defeat depends on this battle. May the General decide!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.69,0:10:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words are enlightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.73,0:11:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I have decided, and will hesitate no longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.73,0:11:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, come, drink a few more cups!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.81,0:11:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I have not ate like this for many days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.30,0:11:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord —
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.24,0:11:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord has fallen for Kǒngmíng's plot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.94,0:11:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.21,0:11:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,If you battle Cáo Cāo, my lord, how do you think you compare to Yuan Shao?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.89,0:12:02.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Back then Cáo Cāo's army was small and his generals few,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.83,0:12:06.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,but he could still wipe out Yuan Shao in one fell swoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.88,0:12:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, today he wields an army of a million to march southward —
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.30,0:12:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,, — how could you take your enemy so lightly?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.50,0:12:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.93,0:12:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, if you listen to the words of Zhuge Liang, and rashly march out —
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.74,0:12:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,, — then it's as if you are putting out a fire while carrying dry twigs on your back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.58,0:12:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,-Indeed, indeed! \N-Lord must reconsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.90,0:12:46.82,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1224,748)}Gù Yōng \NStyled: Yuántàn
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.03,0:12:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Líu Bèi is in defeat and only seeks to borrow the armies of Jiangdong to stop Cáo Cāo's forces!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.44,0:12:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,How could my lord bear to be used by others?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.52,0:13:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Sire!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.89,0:13:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.50,0:13:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, you are sagacious,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.36,0:13:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,— so do not be shaken by those coward gentry who fear death and seek to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.17,0:14:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If my lord hesitates like so, you will used by others
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.23,0:14:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Please retire, and let me think on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.50,0:14:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.63,0:15:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, the State Mother has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.03,0:15:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.87,0:16:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, everything is peaceful here, \Nand you need not worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.82,0:16:17.82,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1160,548)}State Mother Wú
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.28,0:16:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Son, I have heard you do not eat nor drink, and cannot sleep. Is there something troubling you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.32,0:16:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo armies press upon my borders, and seek to devour our Eastern Wú.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.32,0:16:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My military and civil officials cannot decide between peace or war, and debate endlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.19,0:16:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I had thought to fight, but I fear we are outnumbered.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.86,0:16:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I surrender, then I fear that Cáo Cāo would not tolerate my survival, and thus I cannot decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.27,0:16:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you still remember their last words?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.61,0:16:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,'In internal matters, inquire Zhāng Zhāo' —
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.96,0:16:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,— 'In external matters, inquire Zhōu Yú!'
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.92,0:16:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not invite Zhōu Yú here and ask him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.09,0:17:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, mother! In my bustling, I had forgotten his words.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.49,0:17:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Zhongmou, no matter how important the matter, your health is vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If my son ever fell to misfortune —
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.87,0:17:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how could I face our family who have passed?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.37,0:17:22.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Mother, please be at ease, I will send someone to Fanyang —
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.41,0:17:24.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— and invite Gōngjǐng back.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.50,0:17:45.12,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,200,2300,2650)\pos(1186.648,736)}Zhōu Yú \NStyled: Gōngjǐn
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,-My husband!\N-My wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.08,0:17:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.32,0:18:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The lord had just sent someone here, order you to return quickly—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.79,0:18:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,— but you have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.69,0:18:10.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,My dear, Cáo Cāo's army is upon our borders —
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.35,0:18:14.09,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— but sire has not yet decided between peace and war, so I cannot be at ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.73,0:18:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear, you must be tired from the long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.25,0:18:22.21,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1198,722)}Xiǎo Qiáo
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.87,0:18:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear wife, when I rushed back here overnight, all I could think about was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.21,0:18:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You just exaggerate!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.68,0:18:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,As your wife, how could I not know my husband's nature?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.08,0:18:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,For state matters and military duty, you could forget to eat and sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.36,0:18:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How can there be time for his family?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.69,0:18:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Zhang Zhao is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.27,0:18:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You've just come back, and we can't even have a moment of peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.91,0:19:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All right then, tell them to go back, I am going to spend tonight with my wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.75,0:19:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.40,0:19:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.54,0:19:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.90,0:19:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.78,0:19:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.39,0:19:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, you talk first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.09,0:19:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.06,0:19:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Zibu, if you have something to say, please say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, do you know of Jiangdong's current plight?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.17,0:20:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo has a million men, assembled upon the great river.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.78,0:20:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,His war declaration arrived yesterday, inviting our lord to hunt with him at Jiangxia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,While he does mean to devour us, \Nhe has not revealed the intention —
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.39,0:20:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will persuade our lord to surrender tomorrow, to prevent calamity from coming to Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.74,0:20:43.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,But we didn't think Lu Zijing would bring \NLíu Bèi's strategist Zhuge Liang from Jiangxia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They want revenge on Cao army, so purposely used his words to goad my lord
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.05,0:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But Zijing... is blind and stubborn. We wish the Grand Marshal would make his decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.23,0:21:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Does everyone here favor surrendering?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.66,0:21:07.52,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(199.277,742)}Bù Zhì\NStyled: Zǐshān
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.47,0:21:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All of our opinions are the same as Zibu's.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.61,0:21:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I have long favored surrendering.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.95,0:21:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please, go back now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.95,0:21:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When meeting our lord tomorrow morning, I will indeed have something to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.92,0:21:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.52,0:21:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.00,0:21:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Gōngjǐng, do the gentry favor fighting or surrendering?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.07,0:21:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,According to your opinion, my dear, should we fight or surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.54,0:22:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Our lord dominates Jiangdong, and has been established for three generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.09,0:22:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,With the river to the north, and fertile lands to the South,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.53,0:22:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Virtuous lords above, and famed generals below.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.36,0:22:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How could we kneel before the tyrant of the Hàn?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.34,0:22:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheng Pu and other generals have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.56,0:22:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,-Grand Marshal.    \N-Senior General Huang.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.16,0:22:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Senior General Cheng
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.63,0:22:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.94,0:22:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.74,0:22:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, did you know that the southlands are soon to belong to another?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.28,0:23:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.82,0:23:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal—
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.68,0:23:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,— We have built our realm with General Sun —
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.24,0:23:09.20,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,390,3600,4000)\pos(266.091,723.364)}Chéng Pǔ\NStyled: Démóu
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.69,0:23:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,— and fought hundreds of battles large and small to have the six commanderies of Jiangdong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.96,0:23:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, a group of advisors dare to persuade our lord to surrender to Cáo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.53,0:23:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It is shameful! Despicable!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.60,0:23:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We would rather die than surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.64,0:23:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,May the general persuade our lord to plan decisively and muster the armies —
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.74,0:23:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,— so we can do our duty unto death!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.23,0:23:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, do you all agree on this?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.20,0:23:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We would rather die than surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.50,0:23:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Huang Gai can lose my head, but I swear to never kneel and surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.94,0:24:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.71,0:24:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking forward to fight Cáo Cāo, how could I kneel and surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.89,0:24:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Generals, please go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.35,0:24:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait until I have met our lord tomorrow, and I will have an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.53,0:24:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.40,0:24:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.07,0:24:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.41,0:24:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal. My brother Zhuge Liang has arrived from Jiangxia as envoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.78,0:24:38.64,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\fade(255,0,255,0,390,3200,3700)\pos(1172,760)}Zhūgě Jǐn \NStyled: Zǐyú
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.44,0:24:41.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He says Líu Bèi wishes to ally with Eastern Wú, to defeat Cáo Cāo together.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.21,0:24:43.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,The officials have not come to a decision —
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.32,0:24:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,— but because my brother is \Nthe envoy, I dared not say much —
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.82,0:24:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,, — and waited for Grand-Marshal to decide on this matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.93,0:25:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your opinion on this, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.21,0:25:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who surrender find safety.  \NThose who fight... May not survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.25,0:25:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I have made my own decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.33,0:25:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Officials, generals.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.53,0:25:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already chosen between war and peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.33,0:25:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I will discuss this with our lord tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.54,0:25:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.19,0:25:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.66,0:26:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear, I have already seen off the military and civil officials  —
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.06,0:26:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,, —  so no one else will disturb us.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.90,0:26:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps not.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.74,0:26:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, Lu Su has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.01,0:26:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,See?  Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.78,0:26:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The nation is in crisis, \Nand yet you are so relaxed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.52,0:26:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Zijing, you need not say more. Just invite Sir Kǒngmíng here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.35,0:26:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, I will let this fine couple reunite for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.41,0:26:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The strings on the {\i1}qin{\i0}-zither have been neglected thus.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.06,0:27:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear, I am sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.59,0:28:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand-Marshal.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.88,0:28:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.95,0:28:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.92,0:28:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Marshal,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.29,0:28:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now Cáo Cāo's army is gathered on \Nthe river, sire cannot decide at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.23,0:28:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure what the Marshal's opinion is?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.46,0:29:03.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo seized the emperor and commands the lords —
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.35,0:29:06.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,His strength is great \Nand his might cannot be stopped,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.54,0:29:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Fighting will lead to defeat, while surrendering would lead to safety. I've already made up my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.98,0:29:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow when I meet with the lord, envoys shall be sent to offer surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.90,0:29:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir Kǒngmíng, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.30,0:29:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.34,0:29:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You speak wrongly, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.60,0:29:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The realm of Jiangdong was built over three generations, how could it be ceded to another?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.04,0:29:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the very fate of the nation is in just the General's hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.78,0:29:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you listen to the discourse of cowards?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.26,0:29:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Countless lives reside in the six commanderies of the southlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.06,0:29:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If war breaks out, then the people will fall to deprivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.86,0:30:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If I propose war, then would not all the young and old of the southlands heap blame upon me?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.04,0:30:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Wrong. With the general's heroism, \Nand the natural barriers of Eastern Wú —
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.31,0:30:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,— Cáo Cāo may not get his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.65,0:30:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does sir laugh so?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.85,0:30:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I laugh because Zijing refuses to see the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.79,0:30:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does sir laugh at me also?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.56,0:30:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Gōngjǐn's idea to surrender to Cáo Cāo is indeed reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.44,0:30:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo is a master of war, unrivalled in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.34,0:30:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the many heroes who contested him, almost all have perished.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.55,0:30:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Liu of Yu-Province fails to understand this, and fights back—
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.84,0:30:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,— only to fall to routing to Jiangxia, barely alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.36,0:30:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Should the general decide to surrender to Cao.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.76,0:31:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You protect your family on one hand, \Nand on the other can preserve your riches and luxury.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.80,0:31:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord's fate is up to heaven, do we really need to pity him?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.74,0:31:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, do you want my lord to kneel before the nation's villain?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.28,0:31:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not worry, Zijing, I have a plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.71,0:31:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We need neither cede our territory, \Nnor offer our seals and declare servitude —
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.79,0:31:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—in order to drive back Cáo Cāo's million strong host.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.82,0:31:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What brilliant plan do you have, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.30,0:31:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}You merely need to send a single messenger to ferry two persons across the river —
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.04,0:31:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}If Cáo Cāo can have these two, his hordes will furl their banners, and retire from the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.64,0:31:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}The Southland's parting with these two would be no more than a leaf from a tree —
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.14,0:32:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}—or a grain of millet from a granary.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.29,0:32:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Who are these two persons?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.30,0:32:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}When I was in Longzhong—
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.54,0:32:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}—I heard that Cáo Cāo was building a new pavilion near River Zhang.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.04,0:32:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}It was to be named {\i1}'the Bronze Sparrow Terrace'.{\i0} \NA magnificent edifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.04,0:32:20.24,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,AKA. Tóngquètái (铜雀台)
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.97,0:32:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}He sought far and wide for beautiful women to fill its chambers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.68,0:32:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}We know Cáo Cāo as a lecherous man. He has heard patriarch Qiao of Jiangdong has two daughters —
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.90,0:32:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Eldest called 	"Dà Qiáo", younger called "Xiǎo Qiáo".
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.96,0:32:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}— beauties who make birds alight and fishes drown, abash the very blossoms and outshine the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.66,0:32:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Cáo Cāo has once vowed —
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.47,0:32:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}— to have only two dreams; 'To sweep the realm and see the imperial throne in peace —
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.61,0:32:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}—and the sight of those two women\Non the Bronze Sparrow Terraces —
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.98,0:33:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}— and retire in pleasure, and die without regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.15,0:33:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}His million-fold host that threatens Jiangnan, has for its real aim these two women.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.80,0:33:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Why not seek the patriarch Qiao and his daughers with gold, and exchange them over the river?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.97,0:33:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Once has these two, he will be content and return to the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.54,0:33:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}What proof do you have for Cáo Cāo desiring the two Qiaos?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.15,0:33:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Cáo Cāo has a son, {\i1}Cáo Zhí{\i0}, styled {\i1}Zǐjiàn{\i0}.\NA prodigy and a writer of great genius —
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.43,0:33:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}At the command of his father wrote a poem\N{\i1}‘An Ode to the Bronze Sparrow Terrace' —
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.63,0:33:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Its theme the fitness of his house for sovereignty and his possession of the Two Qiaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.24,0:34:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Can sir recite this poem?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.98,0:34:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16} I admired the gorgeous language of this poem, thus I committed it to memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.12,0:34:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}May I request a recitation?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.96,0:34:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}I will try.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.30,0:34:33.18,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Ode to the Bronze Sparrow Terrace ("铜雀台赋")\Nby Cáo Zhí, edited by Luó Guànzhōng
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.30,0:34:30.33,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Beside His Esteemed steps I do rejoice so —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.10,0:34:35.26,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}mounting storied towers in delight —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.68,0:34:40.87,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Peering down on River Zhang's ever-flow —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.98,0:34:45.45,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}whence fruits abundant promise glory —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.12,0:34:50.25,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Aloft rises twin towers either flank —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.76,0:34:54.48,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}one Jade Dragon, and a Phoenix Gold —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.50,0:34:59.99,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}With 'Two Qiaos' holding from Southeast thus —
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.50,0:35:03.98,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: The surname "Qiáo" sounds similar to the word for "bridge", so Cao Cao's words were heard differently by Zhou Yu.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.53,0:35:03.29,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}would joys last dawn to dusk evermore  —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.94,0:35:08.33,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Look upon the royal city's beauty —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.64,0:35:12.30,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}behold the clouds lie floating beneath —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.18,0:35:16.31,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Oh rest, Oh grace! —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.12,0:35:21.29,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}To only be bound by heaven and earth —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.65,0:35:24.98,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}bright as the glory of sun and moon —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.52,0:35:28.56,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Ever honored and ever enduring —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.23,0:35:33.89,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}age immortal as the Father-East —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.37,0:35:40.44,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}May I wish this tower ever standing —
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.41,0:35:45.20,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}for joys of ages never failing!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.01,0:35:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}That bastard Cao dares to mock me!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.72,0:35:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Recall when the Son of Heaven granted a princess of Hàn to wed with Xiongnu for peace—
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.09,0:36:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Why should we miss for two women of the crowd?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.36,0:36:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Sir might not be aware—
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.96,0:36:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\bord16}Da Qiao was the wife of my former lord Sūn Bófú, and Xiao Qiao- !
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.57,0:36:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(726.136,1008.515)}{\bord16}Xiao Qiao is Grand Marshal's very own wife!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.18,0:36:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I truly did not know!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.38,0:36:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My words were poor, it's a crime worthy of death! Please forgive me!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.80,0:36:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.73,0:36:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I swear this world cannot hold both Cáo Cāo and I!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.04,0:36:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Grand Marshal, though this is infuriating, please think carefully before proceeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.86,0:37:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sun Bofu and I have such a deep friendship —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.59,0:37:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,— And now upon me is great responsibility for the state —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.67,0:37:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,— so how could I kneel before Cáo Cāo?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.36,0:37:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To speak frankly, I was merely testing you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.44,0:37:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the moment I left Fanyang, I had already made up my mind to campaign against Cáo Cāo.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.88,0:37:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the path might be filled with blades, I will not waver.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.45,0:37:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,May sir lend me his strength, so we may break Cáo Cāo together.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.43,0:37:45.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If you deem me worthy, I wish to aid you with to my utmost —
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.37,0:37:48.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,— and will be as the Grand Marshal commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.40,0:37:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.11,0:37:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow we will go and see our lord, and discuss the matter of raising an army!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.52,0:38:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.09,0:38:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I have heard all of Kǒngmíng's words back there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.63,0:38:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if Cáo Cāo did not raise his armies specifically for us —
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.66,0:38:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If the southern lands fall, then I fear—
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.76,0:38:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and our children will fall into the hands of the Cáo villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.00,0:39:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife, please don't worry, I will convince my Lord to fight Cáo Cāo
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.01,0:39:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the children asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.26,0:39:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They are asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.64,0:39:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For a great general, yet such a heart for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.02,0:39:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Men are not wood or grass, \Nhow could I be heartless?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.69,0:39:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be giving orders from the terrace, spurring the horses and armies.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.59,0:39:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Above I can return my lord's deep generosity —
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.10,0:40:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,— Below I can bring glory for my wife and family, my life's wishes fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.77,0:40:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I have always loved your talent —
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.38,0:40:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,— and I wish for you to build unparalleled achievements—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.15,0:40:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,— something that I and the children can feel pride for as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.26,0:40:29.99,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Zhuge Liang, in order to unite with Wú to resist Cáo, using his ingenuity—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.60,0:40:35.76,Thinking,NTP,0,0,0,,— cleverly changed the meaning of the "Two Qiáos" in the "Ode to the Bronze Sparrow Terrace."—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.60,0:40:38.60,Thinking,,0,0,0,,—thus enraging Zhōu Yú to act —
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.91,0:40:45.01,Thinking,,0,0,0,,— and revealing his hidden will to challenge Cáo Cāo to the death.
